  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Grant in support of a JDPC staff members&apos; attendance at a Masters programme in Development Studies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Archbishop of Abuja, while serving in the Archdiocese of Jos, requested that CAFOD support the capacity strengthening and professionalisation of JDPC Jos. Through this request, a JDPC staff member and 2 other priests were selected for a Masters&apos; programme. Based on this initial list, the JDPC staff member was originally scheduled to study in South African University while the 2 priests plan to study in Nigeria. It is expected that the JDPC staff would work and be beneficial to JDPC Jos after the training. This project grant is to enable the selected people attend Masters programme. This scholarship grant is necessary to increase the capability of organisations (like JDPC Jos) through training of staff to deliver better and improved programming. 

Initially, CAFOD agreed to sponsor one Candidate for the Masters in South Africa. However, the Masters programme in Kenya was chosen after attempts to gain admission in South Africa failed. Also, the University in Kenya is more affordable than South Africa and furthermore, the programme in Kenya is quite suitable for the candidate seeking for this scholarship. The Masters in Development Studies in Kenya seems to fit the profile of the candidate and equally within the planned timeframe.

Justifications for the change of country location for the Masters programme has been documented, together with the briefs from verbal and face-to-face meetings with the Archbishop.</narrative>
  </description>
